NUMBER 2680
NAME Entry Hall
INDOOR_FLOOR
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This short hallway is paneled in rich, stained oak. Huge uquart beams run
across the hallway, extending to the other portions of the house. Beneath
your feet is a polished, maple floor marred by nary a scratch or scuff. To
the south, a solid oak door leads to the vestibule while at the north end,
an archway leads east into the living room. A hallway runs west to the
rest of the house.
*DESCRIPTION_END
