NUMBER 2681
NAME Living Room
INDOOR_FLOOR
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This magnificent room is where family and friends relax. A solid fireplace
occupies the center of the south wall, uquart beams run overhead and the
maple floor gleams underfoot. Portraits of Cartin Greycloak and Tialuiwen
Cuiviefae are hung with pride above the mantle, flanking the Greycloak
Crest. A broad arch leads out to the hallway and a doorway opens into the
dining room. Two couches and three chairs are arranged in a semicircle
about the fireplace and a long, low coffee-table is conveniently placed for
all to use.
*DESCRIPTION_END
