rosewood table runs almost the entire length of the room. Padded ash
chairs are placed around the table. The Greycloak Crest adorns the wall at
the table's head. On the opposite wall, an elegant maple cabinet holds the
fine crystal, china and flatware used for dinners here. An arch in the
north wall leads to the kitchen and an open doorway in the west wall allows
passage to the living room beyond.
