NUMBER 2688
NAME Shrine
INDOOR_FLOOR
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
CALL 33
*DESCRIPTION_START
This somber room is devoted to the Earthmother, Shemri. The wall opposite
the door has an altar with a silver statue of Shemri. The other three
walls are covered in spectacular mosaics.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 350 VAL2=2687
EXTEND 0 that is cleverly camouflaged
ITEM 1 547
ITEM 2 547
ITEM 3 547
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
A fierce eagle swoops along the face of a mountain-side while in the valley
below a shephard tends to his flock. In a pastoral meadow near the
mountain, a fish leaps high to snap a fly out of the air while a loon
passes overhead.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
A small group of wolflings lead their pups on their first hunt. They
prance and sniff everything in sight, to the amused concern of one of the
females. The leader of the pack has his wise eyes riveted on their prey, a
mighty stag drinking from a bubbling stream. Two of the pups have climbed
on the backs of their mothers for a better view, while another pair flank
the stag with a pair of adults.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
A tribe of plainsmen gather beneath the stars in their dwellings. Warriors
dance to the beat of the elders' drums. Children listen thoughtfully,
while the adolescents mimic their parents' dance in the fringes of the
firelight. The women look on, heads bent together in pairs or threes,
nattering about things that women natter about in every culture.
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
